New York; Norton,  1961/p181.}}}{\f40  
\par }\pard \ql \fi200\li0\ri0\sl480\slmult0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f40 In those days, the crescent of sedimentary basins running east of the Andes, from the }{\i\f40 llanos }{\f40 
 of Venezuela and Colombia to the desert valleys of northwestern Argentina, was seen by some geologists and oil industry executives as a possible source of petroleum potentially as important as the Middle East.}{\cs16\super \chftn {\footnote\ftnalt 
\pard\plain \s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f12\fs20\lang1046\langfe1046\cgrid\langnp1046\langfenp1046 {\cs16\super \chftn }{\f40  Albert J. Brokaw, "Oil," }{\i\f40 Foreign Affairs.  }{\f40 October 1927. }}}{
